Vintage-style illustration of a weathered leather travel bag laying open on a wooden surface, revealing a carefully organized collection of various international power adaptors and charging cables nestled in fabric pockets. A world map partially unfolds beneath the bag, with subtle wear marks and coffee stains suggesting frequent use. Warm amber lighting casts soft shadows, evoking the golden age of travel. The adaptors feature different prong configurations representing UK, European, American, and Australian standards, rendered with nostalgic muted colors and slight film grain texture reminiscent of 1960s travel photography.
